                    <h2>SPD Flag Day helps independence and self-reliance</h2>
                  	<div class="meta">Posted in <a href="#">Template</a>, <a href="#">Freebie</a> | Date: June 18, 2048 | <a href="blog_post.html">180 comments </a></div>
                    
                    <img src="images/captains2.jpg" alt="Image 01" class="image_frame image_fl" />
                    <p align="justify">SPDs main fundraising events Flag Day for people with disabilities.</p>
                    <p align="justify">All the proceeds will be used to provide quality programmes and services for people with disabilities.</p>
                    <p align="justify">Society for the Physically Disabled (SPD), work for the integration of people with physical disabilities into mainstream society. Through many programmes like rehabilitation, employment, training, education, consultation and assessment in assistive technology, day care, and social service support to maximise their potential and to help them to be self-reliant and independent.</p>
                    <p align="justify">(Volunteers are required to be a minimum of 15years of age)The Flag Day event is on 18th of March 2009 at Island-wide, Singapore.</p>
